Package teal.render.primitives

Provides simple geometry primitives that may be used to create shapes within the rendering engine, this abstracts details so that the geometry might be used in other rendering eviornments not limited to Java3D.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Arrow
    This class generates a Rendered arrow, which can be added to the world directly.
    Helix
    This is a Rendered object in the shape of a helix that can be used to represent a spring.
    Line
    Line provides a base class for a group of spatial classes that represent connections between two objects that have a position.
    Sphere  
    Stem
    The Stem class generates a Rendered cylinder that uses the HasFromTo interface used by the Line class.

Package teal.render.primitives Description

Provides simple geometry primitives that may be used to create shapes within the rendering engine, this abstracts details so that the geometry might be used in other rendering eviornments not limited to Java3D. Note that these objects have no physical properties.
